President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in South Carolina and authorized federal aid to assist with recovery efforts in areas affected by Hurricane Dorian. The funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures in several counties. Allan Jarvis has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.